<div id="post-344594" class="blog-post position-4 even-post"><div class="even-post-inner blog-post-inner"><h1 class="title"><a href="http://softwarelivre.org/libreoffice/blog/a-glimpse-at-our-developer-community">A glimpse at our developer community</a></h1><span class="publishing-info"><span class="date">26 de Julho de 2011, 0:00</span><span class="author">, por Software Livre Brasil</span><span class="comments"> - <a href="/libreoffice/blog/a-glimpse-at-our-developer-community#comments_list"><span class='comment-count hide'>0</span><span class='comment-count-write-out'>sem comentários ainda</span></a></span></span><p>Since the start of The Document Foundation, we’ve been aiming for a healthy and vivid ecosystem, for involving many corporate contributors, as well as for strenghtening the volunteer developers. Looking at the current numbers, it becomes obvious that the developer community is indeed well balanced between company-sponsored contributors and independent community volunteers:</p>
<h4>Employers with the most developers (total 300)</h4>
<ul>
<li>(Unknown): 205 (68.3%)</li>
<li>Oracle: 54 (18.0%)</li>
<li>SUSE: 20 (6.7%)</li>
<li>Known contributors: 9 (3.0%)</li>
<li>Canonical: 4 (1.3%)</li>
<li>Redhat: 2 (0.7%)</li>
<li>SIL: 2 (0.7%)</li>
<li>CodeThink: 1 (0.3%)</li>
<li>Bobiciel: 1 (0.3%)</li>
<li>Lanedo: 1 (0.3%)</li>
<li>Tata Consultancy Services: 1 (0.3%)</li>
</ul>
